This file tracks the status of releases in the 1.2.x line.

See "Stabilizing and maintaining releases" in trunk/HACKING for
details on how release lines and voting work, what kinds of bugs can
delay a release, etc.

Status of 1.2.1:
================

Candidate changes:

  * r15088
    Make lock/unlock over ra_dav able to cache authentication data.
    Justfication: Users of locking over http:// will get very annoyed.
    Votes:
      +1: kfogel, sussman, dlr

  * r15082
    Perl bindings, svn_lock_t related accessors.
    Justification: Bindings completeness
    Votes:
      +1: clkao

  * r15080, r15081, r15117
    Perl bindings, call utf_initialize, adjust global pool usage
    Justification: Performance issue for binding users in non-utf8 locale
    Votes:
      +1: clkao

  * r15205
    Fix for ra-dav commits failing when locked paths with
    XML-unsafe names are present (issue #2335).
    Votes:
      +1: cmpilato
      

Approved changes (further review is welcome, but not required):
